      <section name='chat'>

         <para number='1' comment='Hello - having chatted before'>
         "Hello again," says Cedric.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Hello - killed before'>
         "You killed my friend," says the zombie. "That was a rotten thing to do - he was only trying to talk to you. Still, since we all need your help, I'll try not to hold a grudge. My name's Cedric." The zombie looks sheepish. "I know, the name doesn't go with the whole undead thing, does it? But then, I didn't choose to be raised from the dead. It was Count Sinistre who did this to me."
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Hello - captured before'>
         "You tried to capture me. That's not very nice. Still, since we all need your help, I won't hold it against you. My name's Cedric." The zombie looks sheepish. "I know, the name doesn't go with the whole undead thing, does it? But then, I didn't choose to be raised from the dead. It was Count Sinistre who did this to me."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Hello - first time'>
         "Hello," says the zombie. Now it has stopped groaning it doesn't seem to be in the least bit threatening. "My name's Cedric." The zombie looks sheepish. "I know, the name doesn't go with the whole undead thing, does it? But then, I didn't choose to be raised from the dead. It was Count Sinistre who did this to me."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Resistance'>
         There's only a few of us and we're trying to find a way to free the zombies..." Cedric shakes his head. "I can't tell you anything more. Go and see Brian in the castle."
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='sinistre/count'>
         Cedric shivers in what you assume to be terror, which makes a few scaly bits fall off his face in a most disgusting fashion. "He's the owner of this castle; this whole planet, in fact," he explains. "He's got terribly plans for us, which is why we need your help."
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Help/plans'>
         "I can't go into all the details of what Count Sinistre plans to do, and why we are desperate for help - I'm just the messenger," explains Cedric. "You need to talk to Brian."
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Brian'>
         "He's the leader of the zombie resistance," says Cedric. "He stays in the castle."
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Castle'>
         "I can tell you how to get into the castle - there's a secret passageway," says Cedric. "I would show you myself, but Brian told me to stay out here, but it doesn't matter because I can explain it easily."
         </para>

         <para number='10'>
         He points back the way you came. "You need to walk around the wall until you are almost as far as the broken down graveyard wall, and then look at the stones carefully. There's one about head height, on the left, that you will see is a slightly different color from the others. Press it, and a secret door opens that leads into the castle.
         </para>

         <para number='11'>
         "Once you're inside, look around until you find Brian. You don't have to worry about the Count - he's off-planet right now, so you should be safe.
         </para>

         <para number='12'>
         "Good luck."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='Bye'>
         "Goodbye, and say Hi to Brian from me. Good luck."
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='Nomatch'>
         Cedric shrugs, and a vaguely worried frown crosses his brow. "I don't know anything about that," he says. "You'll have to talk to Brian, he's much cleverer than me."
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='Zombie'>
         "It sucks, you know, being a zombie," says Cedric. "I mean, I suppose it beats being completely dead, but we don't last forever either. Our bodies are in a constant state of decay and eventually they fall apart and we die all over again. Plus we can be killed too. If Count Sinistre caught me, that's what he would do."
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='kill'>

         <para number='1' comment='Kill Cedric - have chatted'>
         Why on earth do you want to kill Cedric? You know he's no threat to you!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Already killed him'>
         You killed one zombie and it was replaced by a new one; trying to do it again would be a futile act of meaningless repetition.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Kill him with spade'>
         You batter the zombie to death (or further death) with your spade until it is just a gooey pulp on the ground. The exertion makes you stagger backwards, discarding the spade as you move away from the ugly sight...
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Kill him with rake'>
         You stab at the zombie with your rake, gouging chunks out of its already decaying body, until it is utterly destroyed. The exertion makes you stagger backwards, letting the rake fall onto the ghastly remains...
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='No handy weapon'>
         You don't have anything you could use as a weapon.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='meet'>

         <para number='1' comment='Meet Cedric for first time'>
         Suddenly a figure appears from around a corner, lurching as if unable to control its legs properly, its arms outstretched towards you, making a hideous moaning sound...
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Meet Cedric again'>
         The zombie moves towards you, moaning hideously.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Have tried to catch Cedric'>
         The zombie recognizes you, and moves away so you can't try to lasso it again.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Have killed poor Cedric'>
         You may have killed the zombie, but it clearly wasn't alone and has been replaced by another one! It is looking very angry, perhaps because it had to clear up the remains of your violent and unprovoked attack.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Have spoken to Cedric'>
         Cedric the zombie raises a hand in greeting.
         </para>

