         Unfortunately, the power surge doesn't seem to be strong enough to do any damage. You look closely at the join between the two cables and realize that the power is arcing between some of the bare wires, reducing the efficiency of the circuit. You are going to have to find a way to insulate the cables.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='cable3 - success'>
         You pull the handle down, and the machine starts to hum. Some of the dials light up, and the needles in the gauges move. A crack of lightning hits the lightning rod and surges down the cable into the machine itself.
         </para>

         <para number='9'>
         There is a loud bang, and the front of the machine blows off. The room fills with acrid smoke, and sparks fly out from the exposed inner workings of the machine. The cable fries completely and disintegrates.
         </para>

         <para number='10'>
         Congratulations, you have destroyed the zombie-making machine. Brian will be very pleased.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='Normal operation'>
         You pull the handle down, and the machine starts to hum. Some of the dials light up, and the needles in the gauges move. A crack of lightning hits the lightning rod and surges down to the electrodes, causing sparks to fly across the slab. Now you can see how the machine is supposed to work - you need to come up with a way to sabotage it. Maybe Brian will have some ideas.
         </para>

      </section>

